						"title": "Securing data in SaaS to SaaS applications",
						"subtitle": null,
						"copy": "The [recent Salesloft breach](https://blog.cloudflare.com/response-to-salesloft-drift-incident/) has revealed a critical blind spot for organizations: the lack of visibility into data access by third- and fourth-party applications in enterprise environments. \n\nThe more fourth-party SaaS apps you integrate into your SaaS environments, the larger your attack surface becomes. This leaves security teams with little visibility or control over the data shared with these fourth-party apps, making it difficult to detect or stop a breach.\n\nCloudflare is excited to develop a solution to consolidate all third- and fourth-party connections via a single SaaS-to-SaaS proxy.\n\nSign up to be the first to know when the capabilities are in early access!\n",
